The paper discusses the design and implementation of a distributed graph processing system, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The system is designed to process large-scale graph data, which is commonly found in databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The system also involves communication between nodes, which falls under the category of networked systems and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the system, which is related to system optimization (cs.SI).
